            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">WIRING INFORMATION:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>None required.</para>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">TESTING:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Stop Override Hazard Disabled:</title>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn on the Hazard lights and verify normal operation (flashing), front and rear.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Depress the brake pedal and verify that both front and rear hazard lights remain
                    flashing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <title>Stop Override Hazard Enabled:</title>
            </para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Turn on the Hazard lights and verify normal operation, front and rear.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Depress the brake pedal and verify that both rear stoplights are on (not flashing) and that
                        the front hazard lights remain flashing.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Release the brake pedal and verify that normal operation of the flashing hazards resumes at
                        the rear of the vehicle.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">HOW DO I ADD THIS FEATURE:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>&#8226; If it is desired to have the HAZARD lights override the STOP lights, then the
                Stop_Override_Hazard_Enabled parameter must be turned OFF.
            </para>
